<subSubSection id="70A49AE11B2C36D368CBC4A2D25B8C89" pageId="1" pageNumber="28" type="type material">
<paragraph id="BB9ACDF68078B07887EA5C5FB8D34EF8" pageId="1" pageNumber="28">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BA5904A232EFBB74DFE9AD5DB56DD58B" pageId="1" pageNumber="28">
The male lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="03C55BFBDE56A87221480508984F953D" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Quedius ferox" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferox">Quedius ferox</taxonomicName>
designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="CF6A8D14A5C8C8390AD9E3D0A58CF03D" author="Smetana, A" journalOrPublisher="Mammal Revues" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" url="https://doi.org/10.4039/entm10379fv" year="1971 a">Smetana (1971a)</bibRefCitation>
is deposited in the MCZ (Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard University, Cambridge, United States) and was examined via photographs in the MCZ online type database (http://mczbase.mcz.harvard.edu/name/Quedius%20ferox). Based on the distribution of the lectotype (Enterprise, Florida), pronotum shape and the distinct emargination of male sternite VIII, the name 
<taxonomicName id="5F1AAA64796C1E23C0EA9016DF0764A3" genus="H." lsidName="H. ferox" pageId="1" pageNumber="28" rank="species" species="ferox">H. ferox</taxonomicName>
corresponds to the species restricted to peninsular Florida.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
